Quote:  The speeches were all to the same effect. The substance was this - That Mr. Turton was one of those who had brought them the good tidings ('rongo pai') of the Gospel, and was now forsaking his work to teach them the law; that they could not understand or reconcile this, or as some termed it, worshipping Mammon.
